# Medallion-10: Iteration 33 — gap-free decagonal girih field (2026-05-28)
#
# Per the girih-ceiling decision doc (bikar docs/decisions/2026-05-28-
# medallion10-girih-ceiling.md, Option C″) and the Slice-3 plan
# (bikar .claude/plans/girih-substitution-rule-engine.md): iters 13-18 hit a
# ceiling because the connect-on-circle construction can't produce the
# φ-interlocked overlapping-decagon field the medallion-10 reference actually
# is. iter-33 replaces that approach with the new `girih field decagonal` DSL
# statement (bikar Slice 2, commit ddb2e98), which grows a gap-free field
# outward from a central decagon by attaching tiles to every exposed edge
# (shell-BFS via the tested attachGirihTile seam-solver).
#
# This answers decision-doc Q1: does a real gap-free field clear the A6 zone
# bands, or is A5 (band-network) still the right metric?
#
# DELTA-FROM-ITER-18: total construction change — connect/{10/k}-overlay
# replaced by girih field. Edge length 62 puts the central decagon circumradius
# at ~100 (matches the iter-13..18 C0 radius); shells 2 grows the field to
# ~radius 160 to cover the satellite-rosette ring.

pattern medallion10_iter33
  girih field decagonal 62 shells 2

  # The field emits strapwork segments; voids detect closes them into faces so
  # the gt-emitter has shapes to measure (without this, gt.json has 0 shapes).
  voids detect

  palette medallion_blue
      deep_navy = #091428
      navy = #0D1B3E
      royal = #1B4F72
      cobalt = #2874A6
      turquoise = #48C9B0

  # Classify rules give every face a face_class — bikar's gt-emitter drops
  # unclassified polygons, so without these the field renders but exports 0
  # shapes (the iter-33 first-render finding, 2026-05-28).
  classify .deep_navy where sides == 10
  classify .royal where sides == 4
  classify .turquoise where sides == 3
  classify .cobalt where sides == 5
  classify .navy where sides >= 6

  fill void where sides == 10 color deep_navy
  fill void where sides == 4 color royal
  fill void where sides == 3 color turquoise
  fill void where sides == 5 color cobalt
  fill void where sides >= 6 color navy

  edges color navy width 0.5
